===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# [[hell|Hell]]; the [[bottomless pit]]; [[primeval]] [[chaos]]; a confined subterranean ocean. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{frequently|figurative}} A bottomless or [[unfathomed]] depth, gulf, or [[chasm]]; hence, any deep, [[immeasurable]]; any [[void]] space. {{defdate|First attested in the late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# Anything [[infinite]], immeasurable, or [[profound]]. {{defdate|First attested in the late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# Moral [[depravity]]; vast intellectual or moral depth.
# An impending catastrophic happening.
# {{context|heraldry}} The center of an [[escutcheon]].

